  "summary": "Nick Carraway recounts his summer after moving to West Egg, Long Island, where opulent neighbors and old-money East Egg contrast starkly with new wealth. He narrates Tom and Daisy Buchanan’s gilded restlessness, the polished detachment of Jordan Baker, and the enigmatic Jay Gatsby, whose colossal mansion and extravagant parties mask an obsessive romantic hope tied to Daisy. Through Nick’s reserved perspective the novel examines privilege, moral decay, illusion, and yearning, as surface glamour conceals corruption and vulnerability. Gatsby’s singular capacity for hope stands out amid abortive dreams, social hypocrisy, and the fatal consequences of unmet desire and American modernity's contradictions.",
